+// treated as STALE the moment a NEW HTTP request start is detected on the same
+// keep-alive connection (protocol_detector()==true is the request-boundary
+// signal). The stale entry is dropped and the new request falls through to the
+// find/create path, minting fresh per-request context. This restores v2.6.x
+// one-shot injection semantics, but evicts at the NEXT request boundary
+// instead of immediately after injection, so the entry stays alive within its
+// own request for the generic tracer's client-span emitter to adopt
